Detailed Description

template<class TYPE>
class gaia::base::Vector< TYPE >

This class implements the vector data structure.

The main templated vector class ensuring type safety while making use of VectorImpl. This is the class users want to use.

This class implements templated vector class, which makes use of VectorImpl. Developers should use Vector class instead of VectorImpl.

 // Creates a vector
 Vector<String> vec;
 
 // Adds data into vector
 for (size_t i = 0; i < 50; i++) {
        vec.append(String::valueOf(i));
 }
 
 // Gets vector size
 size_t vec_size = vec.size();
 
 // Inserts item at index 10.
 vec.insert(String::valueOf(2011), 10);

 // Replaces item at index 20.
 vec.replaceAt(String::valueOf(2011), 20);
 
 // Inserts item at index 30.
 vec.insert(String::valueOf(2011), 30);

 // Transforms vector to array.
 Array<String> p_tv = vec.toArray();
 
 // Clears all 
 vec.clear();

template<class TYPE>
void gaia::base::Vector< TYPE >::insertAt ( const TYPE &  prototype_item,
size_t  index,
size_t  numItems = 1 
) [inline]

Inserts the specified item into this vector at the specified location.

This item is inserted before any previous element at the specified location. All elements with an index equal or greater than location have their index increased by 1. If the location is equal to the size of this vector, the item is added at the end. The specified items are initialized from prototype items.

Parameters:
prototype_itemThe item to insert in this vector.
indexThe index at which to insert the element.
numItemsNumber of items to be inserted.
See also:
append
size

Inserts the items in the specified vector at the specified location in this vector.

The items are inserted in the order in which they are returned from the vector iterator. The items with an index equal or higher than vector size have their index increased by the size of the added collection.
